      • sourceSnapshotId

        @Deprecated
public String sourceSnapshotId()
        Deprecated. 
        Returns the service-generated unique id of the snapshot used to create this disk. This value identifies the exact snapshot that was used to create the persistent disk. For example, if you created the persistent disk from a snapshot that was later deleted and recreated under the same name, the source snapshot ID would identify the exact version of the snapshot that was used.

      • getSourceSnapshotId

        public String getSourceSnapshotId()
        Returns the service-generated unique id of the snapshot used to create this disk. This value identifies the exact snapshot that was used to create the persistent disk. For example, if you created the persistent disk from a snapshot that was later deleted and recreated under the same name, the source snapshot ID would identify the exact version of the snapshot that was used.
